==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sagging
<hw>Sag"ging</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A bending or sinking
between the ends of a thing, in consequence of its own, or an imposed,
weight; an arching downward in the middle, as of a ship after straining.
Cf. <er>Hogging</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saginate</ent>⟦br⟧
